  "text": "2. The distribution of NPIs in JA JA shows two classes of NPIs: (i) NPIs that are only licensed in the domain of sentential negation, and (ii) NPIs that are licensed in the domain of DE operators. [CITATION_1] The same locality constraint applies to the restriction of the universal quantifier koll 'all'. Note that while it is grammatical for a weak NPI to appear in a clause that restricts the universal quantifier (50a), it is ungrammatical for it to appear in a clause embedded further in the restricting clause (50b). (50) ",
